		{"id":"76a72ecdb957f6e5","type":"text","text":"The TM guesses a word $w$ and keeps track of the Reachable States.\nMaking sure to never reach final and nonfinal at the same time","x":420,"y":-1760,"width":360,"height":180},
		{"id":"b1ef175851b8d621","type":"text","text":"PSPACE = NPSPACE => PSPACE = coPSPACE","x":-220,"y":-1700,"width":250,"height":60},
		{"id":"42c5fa6dd5dfc7b0","type":"file","file":"Automata/NFA non-universality is in PSPACE.md","x":510,"y":-1420,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"a4fccc5bdf9773e3","type":"text","text":"Muller Automata\n\nA Muller condition $F$ over a state set $Q$ is a subset $F \\subseteq 2^Q$.\nA run $\\rho$ is accepted by a Muller Automaton if $inf(\\rho) \\in F$\n$$inf(\\rho) = \\{q \\in Q | \\exists^\\infty i. \\rho(i) = q\\}$$\nThe set of all infinitely visited states is in $F$.","x":445,"y":3405,"width":430,"height":280},
		{"id":"9ddfb6519b4943f0","type":"text","text":"Given Muller family $\\mathcal{F} \\subseteq 2^Q$.\nConstruct\n$\\mathcal{R} = \\{(Q \\setminus S,\\ S) \\mid S \\in \\mathcal{F}\\}$","x":790,"y":3785,"width":300,"height":160},
		{"id":"0d613ff41f9e5cd8","type":"text","text":"Rabin Automata\n\nA Rabin condition $\\mathcal{F} \\subseteq E \\times F$ with $E, F \\subseteq Q$, is accepting a run $\\rho$ if there is $(E, F) \\in \\mathcal{F}$ with\n$$inf(\\rho) \\cap F \\not = \\emptyset \\land inf(\\rho) \\cap E = \\emptyset$$\nThere is at least one state from $F$ that is infinitely often visted and no state in $E$ is visited infinitely often\n","x":682,"y":4105,"width":385,"height":290},
		{"id":"92efefd11a9ce0cd","type":"text","text":"Parity Automata\n\nA parity condition is a coloring function on the state set \n$c: Q \\to \\{0, ..., k \\}$ \nA run $\\rho\\in Q^\\omega$ satisfies the parity condition if \n$$max inf(c(\\rho)) \\mod 2 \\equiv 0$$\nThe maximum color that appears infinitely often is even","x":1440,"y":3388,"width":420,"height":315},
		{"id":"0648b3756022ce77","type":"text","text":"DBA","x":1130,"y":2995,"width":250,"height":60},
		{"id":"02a9ecedae5d8594","type":"text","text":"NBA","x":535,"y":3000,"width":250,"height":60},
		{"id":"d50ac78a0e594b5e","type":"text","text":"$\\mathcal{R} = \\{(E_i, F_i)\\}_{i=1}^k$\n\n$$\\mathcal{F} =\n\\big\\{\nS \\subseteq Q\n\\mid\n\\exists i:\nS \\cap E_i = \\emptyset\n\\ \\land\\\nS \\cap F_i \\neq \\emptyset\n\\big\\}$$\n","x":275,"y":3785,"width":387,"height":160},
		{"id":"fcb96d295e85cc11","type":"file","file":"Automata/MSO <=> w-Regular.md","x":-765,"y":2820,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"c00f2c9c8295f285","type":"file","file":"Automata/w-Regular <=> NBA.md","x":-115,"y":2335,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"127ad64a257a3bb1","type":"file","file":"Automata/w-Regular Languages.md","x":460,"y":1905,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"400a5e7a8f42c9e4","type":"file","file":"Automata/NBA complementation.md","x":890,"y":2365,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"62526b7a7ae7de6a","type":"text","text":"$\\omega$-Regular Languages","x":-490,"y":2305,"width":250,"height":60},
		{"id":"51a276b1b53b67cb","type":"text","text":"Streett Automata\n\n$\\rho \\in Q^\\omega$ is accepting if for all $(E, F) \\in\\mathcal{F}$\n$$inf(\\rho) \\cap F = \\emptyset \\implies inf(\\rho) \\cap E \\not = \\emptyset$$\nIf $F_i$ is visited infinitely often $E_i$ is visted infinitely often.\nIt is the dual of a Rabin Automata","x":-320,"y":4093,"width":375,"height":315},
		{"id":"520af214ec0435cd","type":"file","file":"Automata/Streett => NBA.md","x":-200,"y":3385,"width":400,"height":415},
